	abstract = {A dwarf spring wheat (Triticum aestivum ‘Yecora 70’) was grown under irrigation and optimal agronomy in northwest Mexico during four winter seasons. Single shading treatments of approximately four (1971, 1972), three (1973), and two (1974) weeks duration and various intensities were used to elucidate the importance for grain yield of radiation and crop photosynthesis at different stages of development. 
